Real Company Scenarios (Asked in Interviews)

Scenario: “Production Web Application Down”
You check:
Firewall
Nginx/Apache
DNS
Routing
Load balancer health checks
SSL certificate
Disk full issue
Network latency or packet drop

Scenario: “Two Microservices cannot talk to each other”

Check:
Pod IP / service IP
Firewall/iptables
Port open or not
DNS inside Kubernetes:
## kubectl exec <pod> -- nslookup service-name


Service type: ClusterIP / NodePort

SELinux

Scenario: “SSH not working in Production”

Check:

systemctl status sshd
ss -tulnp | grep 22
firewall-cmd --list-all
fail2ban status


Fix based on issue.

Scenario: “Server unreachable after IP change”

Fix:

nmcli con mod eth0 connection.autoconnect yes
nmcli con up eth0
